{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"When we park in a big parking lot,"},{"time":2000,"text":"how do we remember where we parked our car?"},{"time":4000,"text":"Here's the problem facing Homer."},{"time":7000,"text":"And we're going to try to understand"},{"time":9000,"text":"what's happening in his brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":11000,"text":"So we'll start with the hippocampus, shown in yellow,"},{"time":13000,"text":"which is the organ of memory."},{"time":15000,"text":"If you have damage there, like in Alzheimer's,"},{"time":17000,"text":"you can't remember things including where you parked your car."},{"time":19000,"text":"It's named after Latin for \"seahorse,\""},{"time":21000,"text":"which it resembles."},{"time":23000,"text":"And like the rest of the brain, it's made of neurons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":25000,"text":"So the human brain"},{"time":27000,"text":"has about a hundred billion neurons in it."},{"time":29000,"text":"And the neurons communicate with each other"},{"time":32000,"text":"by sending little pulses or spikes of electricity"},{"time":34000,"text":"via connections to each other."},{"time":36000,"text":"The hippocampus is formed of two sheets of cells,"},{"time":39000,"text":"which are very densely interconnected."},{"time":41000,"text":"And scientists have begun to understand"},{"time":43000,"text":"how spatial memory works"},{"time":45000,"text":"by recording from individual neurons"},{"time":47000,"text":"in rats or mice"},{"time":49000,"text":"while they forage or explore an environment"},{"time":51000,"text":"looking for food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"So we're going to imagine we're recording from a single neuron"},{"time":56000,"text":"in the hippocampus of this rat here."},{"time":59000,"text":"And when it fires a little spike of electricity,"},{"time":61000,"text":"there's going to be a red dot and a click."},{"time":64000,"text":"So what we see"},{"time":66000,"text":"is that this neuron knows"},{"time":68000,"text":"whenever the rat has gone into one particular place in its environment."},{"time":71000,"text":"And it signals to the rest of the brain"},{"time":73000,"text":"by sending a little electrical spike."},{"time":76000,"text":"So we could show the firing rate of that neuron"},{"time":79000,"text":"as a function of the animal's location."},{"time":81000,"text":"And if we record from lots of different neurons,"},{"time":83000,"text":"we'll see that different neurons fire"},{"time":85000,"text":"when the animal goes in different parts of its environment,"},{"time":87000,"text":"like in this square box shown here."},{"time":89000,"text":"So together they form a map"},{"time":91000,"text":"for the rest of the brain,"},{"time":93000,"text":"telling the brain continually,"},{"time":95000,"text":"\"Where am I now within my environment?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":97000,"text":"Place cells are also being recorded in humans."},{"time":100000,"text":"So epilepsy patients sometimes need"},{"time":102000,"text":"the electrical activity in their brain monitoring."},{"time":105000,"text":"And some of these patients played a video game"},{"time":107000,"text":"where they drive around a small town."},{"time":109000,"text":"And place cells in their hippocampi would fire, become active,"},{"time":112000,"text":"start sending electrical impulses"},{"time":115000,"text":"whenever they drove through a particular location in that town."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"So how does a place cell know"},{"time":120000,"text":"where the rat or person is within its environment?"},{"time":123000,"text":"Well these two cells here"},{"time":125000,"text":"show us that the boundaries of the environment"},{"time":127000,"text":"are particularly important."},{"time":129000,"text":"So the one on the top"},{"time":131000,"text":"likes to fire sort of midway between the walls"},{"time":133000,"text":"of the box that their rat's in."},{"time":135000,"text":"And when you expand the box, the firing location expands."},{"time":138000,"text":"The one below likes to fire"},{"time":140000,"text":"whenever there's a wall close by to the south."},{"time":143000,"text":"And if you put another wall inside the box,"},{"time":145000,"text":"then the cell fires in both place"},{"time":147000,"text":"wherever there's a wall to the south"},{"time":149000,"text":"as the animal explores around in its box."},{"time":153000,"text":"So this predicts"},{"time":155000,"text":"that sensing the distances and directions of boundaries around you --"},{"time":157000,"text":"extended buildings and so on --"},{"time":159000,"text":"is particularly important for the hippocampus."},{"time":162000,"text":"And indeed, on the inputs to the hippocampus,"},{"time":164000,"text":"cells are found which project into the hippocampus,"},{"time":166000,"text":"which do respond exactly"},{"time":168000,"text":"to detecting boundaries or edges"},{"time":171000,"text":"at particular distances and directions"},{"time":173000,"text":"from the rat or mouse"},{"time":175000,"text":"as it's exploring around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177000,"text":"So the cell on the left, you can see,"},{"time":179000,"text":"it fires whenever the animal gets near"},{"time":181000,"text":"to a wall or a boundary to the east,"},{"time":184000,"text":"whether it's the edge or the wall of a square box"},{"time":187000,"text":"or the circular wall of the circular box"},{"time":189000,"text":"or even the drop at the edge of a table, which the animals are running around."},{"time":192000,"text":"And the cell on the right there"},{"time":194000,"text":"fires whenever there's a boundary to the south,"},{"time":196000,"text":"whether it's the drop at the edge of the table or a wall"},{"time":198000,"text":"or even the gap between two tables that are pulled apart."},{"time":201000,"text":"So that's one way in which we think"},{"time":203000,"text":"place cells determine where the animal is as it's exploring around."}]},{"cues":[{"time":206000,"text":"We can also test where we think objects are,"},{"time":209000,"text":"like this goal flag, in simple environments --"},{"time":212000,"text":"or indeed, where your car would be."},{"time":214000,"text":"So we can have people explore an environment"},{"time":217000,"text":"and see the location they have to remember."},{"time":220000,"text":"And then, if we put them back in the environment,"},{"time":222000,"text":"generally they're quite good at putting a marker down"},{"time":224000,"text":"where they thought that flag or their car was."},{"time":227000,"text":"But on some trials,"},{"time":229000,"text":"we could change the shape and size of the environment"},{"time":231000,"text":"like we did with the place cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233000,"text":"In that case, we can see"},{"time":235000,"text":"how where they think the flag had been changes"},{"time":238000,"text":"as a function of how you change the shape and size of the environment."},{"time":241000,"text":"And what you see, for example,"},{"time":243000,"text":"if the flag was where that cross was in a small square environment,"},{"time":246000,"text":"and then if you ask people where it was,"},{"time":248000,"text":"but you've made the environment bigger,"},{"time":250000,"text":"where they think the flag had been"},{"time":252000,"text":"stretches out in exactly the same way"},{"time":254000,"text":"that the place cell firing stretched out."},{"time":256000,"text":"It's as if you remember where the flag was"},{"time":258000,"text":"by storing the pattern of firing across all of your place cells"},{"time":261000,"text":"at that location,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and then you can get back to that location"},{"time":265000,"text":"by moving around"},{"time":267000,"text":"so that you best match the current pattern of firing of your place cells"},{"time":269000,"text":"with that stored pattern."},{"time":271000,"text":"That guides you back to the location that you want to remember."}]},{"cues":[{"time":274000,"text":"But we also know where we are through movement."},{"time":277000,"text":"So if we take some outbound path --"},{"time":279000,"text":"perhaps we park and we wander off --"},{"time":281000,"text":"we know because our own movements,"},{"time":283000,"text":"which we can integrate over this path"},{"time":285000,"text":"roughly what the heading direction is to go back."},{"time":287000,"text":"And place cells also get this kind of path integration input"},{"time":291000,"text":"from a kind of cell called a grid cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294000,"text":"Now grid cells are found, again,"},{"time":296000,"text":"on the inputs to the hippocampus,"},{"time":298000,"text":"and they're a bit like place cells."},{"time":300000,"text":"But now as the rat explores around,"},{"time":302000,"text":"each individual cell fires"},{"time":304000,"text":"in a whole array of different locations"},{"time":307000,"text":"which are laid out across the environment"},{"time":309000,"text":"in an amazingly regular triangular grid."},{"time":314000,"text":"And if you record from several grid cells --"},{"time":317000,"text":"shown here in different colors --"},{"time":319000,"text":"each one has a grid-like firing pattern across the environment,"},{"time":322000,"text":"and each cell's grid-like firing pattern is shifted slightly"},{"time":325000,"text":"relative to the other cells."},{"time":327000,"text":"So the red one fires on this grid"},{"time":329000,"text":"and the green one on this one and the blue on on this one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":332000,"text":"So together, it's as if the rat"},{"time":335000,"text":"can put a virtual grid of firing locations"},{"time":337000,"text":"across its environment --"},{"time":339000,"text":"a bit like the latitude and longitude lines that you'd find on a map,"},{"time":342000,"text":"but using triangles."},{"time":344000,"text":"And as it moves around,"},{"time":346000,"text":"the electrical activity can pass"},{"time":348000,"text":"from one of these cells to the next cell"},{"time":350000,"text":"to keep track of where it is,"},{"time":352000,"text":"so that it can use its own movements"},{"time":354000,"text":"to know where it is in its environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"Do people have grid cells?"},{"time":358000,"text":"Well because all of the grid-like firing patterns"},{"time":360000,"text":"have the same axes of symmetry,"},{"time":362000,"text":"the same orientations of grid, shown in orange here,"},{"time":365000,"text":"it means that the net activity"},{"time":367000,"text":"of all of the grid cells in a particular part of the brain"},{"time":370000,"text":"should change"},{"time":372000,"text":"according to whether we're running along these six directions"},{"time":374000,"text":"or running along one of the six directions in between."},{"time":377000,"text":"So we can put people in an MRI scanner"},{"time":379000,"text":"and have them do a little video game"},{"time":381000,"text":"like the one I showed you"},{"time":383000,"text":"and look for this signal."},{"time":385000,"text":"And indeed, you do see it in the human entorhinal cortex,"},{"time":388000,"text":"which is the same part of the brain that you see grid cells in rats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":391000,"text":"So back to Homer."},{"time":393000,"text":"He's probably remembering where his car was"},{"time":395000,"text":"in terms of the distances and directions"},{"time":397000,"text":"to extended buildings and boundaries"},{"time":399000,"text":"around the location where he parked."},{"time":401000,"text":"And that would be represented"},{"time":403000,"text":"by the firing of boundary-detecting cells."},{"time":405000,"text":"He's also remembering the path he took out of the car park,"},{"time":408000,"text":"which would be represented in the firing of grid cells."},{"time":411000,"text":"Now both of these kinds of cells"},{"time":413000,"text":"can make the place cells fire."},{"time":415000,"text":"And he can return to the location where he parked"},{"time":417000,"text":"by moving so as to find where it is"},{"time":420000,"text":"that best matches the firing pattern"},{"time":422000,"text":"of the place cells in his brain currently"},{"time":424000,"text":"with the stored pattern where he parked his car."},{"time":427000,"text":"And that guides him back to that location"},{"time":429000,"text":"irrespective of visual cues"},{"time":431000,"text":"like whether his car's actually there."},{"time":433000,"text":"Maybe it's been towed."},{"time":435000,"text":"But he knows where it was, so he knows to go and get it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":438000,"text":"So beyond spatial memory,"},{"time":440000,"text":"if we look for this grid-like firing pattern"},{"time":442000,"text":"throughout the whole brain,"},{"time":444000,"text":"we see it in a whole series of locations"},{"time":447000,"text":"which are always active"},{"time":449000,"text":"when we do all kinds of autobiographical memory tasks,"},{"time":451000,"text":"like remembering the last time you went to a wedding, for example."},{"time":454000,"text":"So it may be that the neural mechanisms"},{"time":456000,"text":"for representing the space around us"},{"time":459000,"text":"are also used for generating visual imagery"},{"time":463000,"text":"so that we can recreate the spatial scene, at least,"},{"time":466000,"text":"of the events that have happened to us when we want to imagine them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"So if this was happening,"},{"time":471000,"text":"your memories could start by place cells activating each other"},{"time":474000,"text":"via these dense interconnections"},{"time":476000,"text":"and then reactivating boundary cells"},{"time":478000,"text":"to create the spatial structure"},{"time":480000,"text":"of the scene around your viewpoint."},{"time":482000,"text":"And grid cells could move this viewpoint through that space."},{"time":484000,"text":"Another kind of cell, head direction cells,"},{"time":486000,"text":"which I didn't mention yet,"},{"time":488000,"text":"they fire like a compass according to which way you're facing."},{"time":491000,"text":"They could define the viewing direction"},{"time":493000,"text":"from which you want to generate an image for your visual imagery,"},{"time":496000,"text":"so you can imagine what happened when you were at this wedding, for example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499000,"text":"So this is just one example"},{"time":501000,"text":"of a new era really"},{"time":503000,"text":"in cognitive neuroscience"},{"time":505000,"text":"where we're beginning to understand"},{"time":507000,"text":"psychological processes"},{"time":509000,"text":"like how you remember or imagine or even think"},{"time":512000,"text":"in terms of the actions"},{"time":514000,"text":"of the billions of individual neurons that make up our brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}